{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Ibn Majah","section":{"33":{"eng-name":"Etiquette","ara-name":"كتاب الأدب"}},"section_detail":{"33":{"hadithnumber_first":3657,"hadithnumber_last":3826,"arabicnumber_first":3657,"arabicnumber_last":3826}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":3708,"arabicnumber":3708,"text":"It was narrated that Ali said:\"I had two times of visiting the Messenger of Allah(ﷺ), at night and during the day. If I came to him when he was praying, he would clear his throat (to let me know he was praying)","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Daif"},{"name":"Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi","grade":"Daif"},{"name":"Shuaib Al Arnaut","grade":"Daif"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Daif"}],"reference":{"book":33,"hadith":52},"chapter":{"id":17,"ara-name":"باب الاِسْتِئْذَانِ","eng-name":"Seeking Permission to Enter","isFirstHadith":false}}]}